It is a sadly ironic aspect of social media that the people who proclaim loudest that they can’t trust the “MSM” (mainstream media) are the ones who put their trust in the wildest sort of illogical fake news on the internet. And the Covid-19 threat and the measures taken to slow the spread of the virus have been a golden opportunity for the tin foil hat-wearing conspiracy theorists to start spreading alarmist rubbish. Flavour of the month in the past fortnight has been “The Chinese are invading!” type of posts on Facebook and Twitter. Using photos of Chinese military parades...